<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="341" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1543.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-09-23"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 23, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 7th instant, No. 1039, and the copy of correspondence
                            respecting the schooner St. Mary’s which accompanied it.</p>
                        <p>Your note to Earl Russell is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., London.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>